106
00:02:45,770 --> 00:02:47,920
Phew, thank goodness.

107
00:02:45,910 --> 00:02:50,180
[Wearing a different costume]
[Kagura]

108
00:02:48,190 --> 00:02:50,660
I wasn't sure what I'd do if we stayed like this till the end.

109
00:02:50,310 --> 00:02:52,180
[Gintoki]

110
00:02:50,660 --> 00:02:52,450
Hey, Kagura. When did you change?

111
00:02:52,420 --> 00:02:55,320
[Shinpachi]

112
00:02:52,580 --> 00:02:55,610
Oh, that's a retake of the wrong costume.

113
00:02:55,650 --> 00:02:58,020
[Kagura]

114
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:58,470
Come to think of it, Gin-chan, you look different, too.

115
00:02:58,290 --> 00:02:58,660
[Gintoki]

116
00:02:58,470 --> 00:02:59,110
Huh?

117
00:02:58,920 --> 00:03:01,290
[Shinpachi]

118
00:02:59,310 --> 00:03:01,480
The animation director has yet to correct the key animations.

119
00:03:01,530 --> 00:03:03,930
[Kagura]

120
00:03:02,860 --> 00:03:04,290
You look weird!

121
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:10,030
[Gintoki]

122
00:03:04,290 --> 00:03:06,400
Dammit, what's happening here?

123
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:10,220
Oh man, what the heck is this? We've turned into very simple drawings.

124
00:03:10,430 --> 00:03:14,440
[Shinpachi]

125
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:14,420
Oh, looks like even the key animation isn't done on time and all we have are the rough drafts.

126
00:03:14,660 --> 00:03:17,330
You can't tell who's who anymore.

127
00:03:14,670 --> 00:03:17,040
[Kagura]

128
00:03:17,310 --> 00:03:25,820
[Gintoki]

129
00:03:17,330 --> 00:03:19,760
Dammit. Who's responsible for this?

130
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,400
Who's the one who lost the schedule so the storyboard was late?

131
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:24,320
I'll tell the director and have him fired.

132
00:03:24,460 --> 00:03:25,860
Who the hell was it?

133
00:03:27,050 --> 00:03:28,320
[Shinpachi]

134
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:28,280
It was the director himself!

135
00:03:56,000 --> 00:04:16,000
[Gintoki]

136
00:04:57,070 --> 00:05:01,380
[Taizo Hasegawa (38 years old), also known as Madao has finally found a new job.]

137
00:05:01,380 --> 00:05:07,020
[If he can lead a steady life with this job, then there's something he's decided to do...]

138
00:05:19,580 --> 00:05:20,180
Hello.

139
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:22,550
Oh, it's me.

140
00:05:23,210 --> 00:05:26,970
How unusual for you to call me.

141
00:05:27,770 --> 00:05:28,910
Did something happen?

142
00:05:28,910 --> 00:05:30,580
No, not especially...

143
00:05:31,460 --> 00:05:33,650
I can't call you unless something bad has happened?

144
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:36,320
Oh my, do you have to talk to me like that?

145
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:38,890
Are you calling to pick a fight with me?

146
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:41,450
Are you eating well?

147
00:05:42,070 --> 00:05:44,410
You can't just eat fast food boxed lunches, you know.

148
00:05:44,410 --> 00:05:47,370
Oh, cut that out. I'm not a kid, you know.

149
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:51,910
I know. You're a full-fledged adult. That's why you need to eat properly.

150
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:55,310
So? What happened?

151
00:05:55,310 --> 00:05:56,150
Huh?

152
00:05:56,150 --> 00:05:58,050
Something good happened, right?

153
00:05:58,290 --> 00:06:04,790
It's nothing special...it's just that, I...

154
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:06,500
...found a job.

155
00:06:06,790 --> 00:06:09,010
Really? Congratulations!

156
00:06:09,370 --> 00:06:13,630
It's nothing that spectacular, but at least it's a stable job.

157
00:06:13,850 --> 00:06:15,930
Really? That's wonderful.

158
00:06:16,490 --> 00:06:18,550
This calls for a celebration.

159
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:22,850
Never mind that. It's not like this is my first job or anything.

160
00:06:23,410 --> 00:06:25,470
That's okay. Let me treat you.

161
00:06:25,970 --> 00:06:31,450
I couldn't do anything for you when you were down-and-out.

162
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,790
Hatsu... Um...

163
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:44,680
Once I start this job and my life becomes stable, can you and I...start over...?

164
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:45,690
Hatsu-san.

165
00:06:47,180 --> 00:06:48,710
Are you enjoying the night view?

166
00:06:49,740 --> 00:06:51,450
Ah... I'm sorry, I'll call you later.

167
00:06:51,670 --> 00:06:52,520
Huh? Hey, wait-

168
00:07:05,950 --> 00:07:07,570
Huh? A man?

169
00:07:08,380 --> 00:07:11,180
I'm pretty sure it was a man's voice.

170
00:07:11,900 --> 00:07:14,930
As soon as she heard his voice, she hung up.

171
00:07:15,590 --> 00:07:19,320
What's going on? Is that guy more important than me?

172
00:07:19,820 --> 00:07:21,420
That's adultery. Adultery!

173
00:07:22,090 --> 00:07:26,170
Adultery? But weren't you two divorced a long time ago?

174
00:07:26,550 --> 00:07:29,780
Don't be disrespectful! We've just been separated.

175
00:07:30,180 --> 00:07:32,420
I don't remember putting my seal on any divorce papers.

176
00:07:33,430 --> 00:07:34,840
You want me to investigate an extramarital affair?

177
00:07:35,790 --> 00:07:37,720
I'm really not interested since I know you and all.

178
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:38,730
I'll pay you well.

179
00:07:39,100 --> 00:07:40,600
I'm no longer just a freelancer, you know.

180
00:07:41,640 --> 00:07:43,400
No longer just a freelancer?

181
00:07:44,510 --> 00:07:47,770
You're working for some loser ol' man that you hit it off with at some bar, right?

182
00:07:47,770 --> 00:07:48,900
You sure he's reliable?

183
00:07:49,050 --> 00:07:50,660
Don't be rude.

184
00:07:50,980 --> 00:07:53,490
True, it may not be a top-notch firm,

185
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:57,540
but it's rare these days to find a company that lets me wear sunglasses to work.

186
00:07:57,890 --> 00:08:03,390
You sure all their workers don't wear sunglasses and sell white powder?

187
00:08:03,390 --> 00:08:07,060
How did you know? They also sell something called "chaka."

188
00:08:03,390 --> 00:08:08,910
[Note: Chaka is gangster slang for "gun."]

189
00:08:07,060 --> 00:08:08,910
Not sure what that is.

190
00:08:09,910 --> 00:08:11,430
I think you should quit.

191
00:08:11,430 --> 00:08:12,440
Don't worry about it.

192
00:08:13,070 --> 00:08:17,370
Anyone who wears sunglasses can't be bad. They're just shy.

193
00:08:17,840 --> 00:08:21,450
Shy guys don't wear such embarrassingly short pants.

194
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:26,320
Shut up. Hatsu bought me this suit when I first got a job.

195
00:08:28,970 --> 00:08:31,910
Humph. If you keep thinking about your woman,

196
00:08:31,910 --> 00:08:35,440
you'll fail at your new job again and screw up any chance of getting back together with her.

197
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:41,420
Leave that part of your life to me and you just focus on not getting fired, okay?

198
00:08:43,220 --> 00:08:44,390
...Thanks.

199
00:08:46,750 --> 00:08:48,540
Gin-san, I'm gonna do it.

200
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:51,970
This time, I'm gonna find happiness for sure.

201
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:54,560
Don't screw it up now.

202
00:08:59,090 --> 00:08:59,860
Huh?

203
00:09:41,020 --> 00:09:42,400
Pervert!

204
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:43,890
No, no. This is...

205
00:09:43,890 --> 00:09:46,790
It's the Kinniku Buster! Kinniku Buster!

206
00:09:43,890 --> 00:09:46,790
[Note: Kinnikuman's trademark attack and one of 48 killer moves. From Ultimate Muscle.]

207
00:09:46,930 --> 00:09:49,930
[Edo Police]

208
00:09:49,930 --> 00:09:51,660
[Interview room 1]

209
00:09:57,880 --> 00:09:59,560
Did you bring me a rope?

210
00:10:00,450 --> 00:10:03,280
A strong one that won't break even if a person hangs from it.

211
00:10:03,680 --> 00:10:07,880
No, they were all sold out. But instead...

212
00:10:07,880 --> 00:10:08,510
...Here take this.

213
00:10:08,510 --> 00:10:10,260
The investigation report on your wife.

214
00:10:10,570 --> 00:10:12,220
Go ahead and check it with your own eyes.

215
00:10:15,150 --> 00:10:17,240
Is she guilty or not?

216
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:18,830
Something good is bound to happen if you're alive.

217
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:21,550
Is she guilty or not?

218
00:10:21,550 --> 00:10:23,600
Tomorrow is another day.

219
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:25,240
I'm asking you, is she guilty or not?

220
00:10:25,700 --> 00:10:26,760
Hey? Did you get a haircut?

221
00:10:25,700 --> 00:10:30,110
[Note: Spoof of Cozy Tomita, who impersonates Tamori.]

222
00:10:27,130 --> 00:10:30,110
Kill me! Just kill me!

223
00:10:30,110 --> 00:10:34,730
Even if I'm alive, I'm just destined to dance a bloody rondo all my life.

224
00:10:35,010 --> 00:10:38,900
I'll have to keep climbing a tortuous spiral staircase.

225
00:10:38,900 --> 00:10:41,050
Just end it all for me.

226
00:10:41,630 --> 00:10:45,240
I'm sure you guys suspect me of performing lewd sex acts.

227
00:10:45,930 --> 00:10:47,260
I don't blame you.

228
00:10:47,720 --> 00:10:50,870
After all, my own wife walked out on me!

229
00:10:51,300 --> 00:10:54,280
The train almost hit us and before I knew it, I was doing the Kinniku Buster move.

230
00:10:54,620 --> 00:10:57,390
But you wouldn't believe that anyway, right?

231
00:10:57,660 --> 00:11:00,440
Total strangers like you guys would never believe

232
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:03,110
I'm innocent or that it was an accident, right?

233
00:11:04,750 --> 00:11:06,810
You idiot!

234
00:11:08,620 --> 00:11:10,430
What the hell are you doing?

235
00:11:11,210 --> 00:11:16,840
Total strangers? If I thought that way, I wouldn't be here.

236
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:19,830
If I thought of you as a total stranger,

237
00:11:19,830 --> 00:11:21,880
then I wouldn't give a damn which slammer you're in...

238
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:23,080
...or if you're dead!

239
00:11:24,640 --> 00:11:26,190
If I thought of you as a total stranger...

240
00:11:27,610 --> 00:11:30,220
...then I wouldn't borrow or lend you this!

241
00:11:30,220 --> 00:11:31,910
You totally suspect me!

242
00:11:31,910 --> 00:11:33,760
It's confirmed now.

243
00:11:33,540 --> 00:11:45,420
[The Pervert]

244
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:35,010
It's not like that, okay?

245
00:11:35,230 --> 00:11:37,760
I can differentiate between fiction and reality.

246
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:39,940
I'm innocent!

247
00:11:39,940 --> 00:11:41,020
I know, I know.

248
00:11:41,020 --> 00:11:42,650
I believe you. I believe you. Believe!

249
00:11:42,650 --> 00:11:45,400
Really. You really believe me, right?

250
00:11:45,780 --> 00:11:50,760
God, enough already. He said he believes you, didn't he? Man, you're gross.

251
00:11:50,760 --> 00:11:52,940
That's not the face of trust.

252
00:11:53,150 --> 00:11:55,130
She's looking at me like I'm trash.

253
00:11:55,450 --> 00:11:59,660
You're wrong. Girls this age are sensitive to stuff like that.

254
00:11:59,870 --> 00:12:02,450
Hey, don't get too close, Kagura. He's dangerous.

255
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:07,250
Hasegawa-san, is the investigation still going on?

256
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:11,050
Yeah, today's the seventh day.

257
00:12:11,570 --> 00:12:14,010
Although I feel more like I'm being threatened than investigated...

258
00:12:14,780 --> 00:12:18,310
I've been denying the allegations, but my mind and body are at its limit.

259
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:20,800
Honestly, I don't think I can take anymore.

260
00:12:21,190 --> 00:12:22,640
Huh? You did it, didn't you?

261
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:24,010
The Kinniku Buster!

262
00:12:24,660 --> 00:12:27,790
Now that Hatsu, my last sanctuary, has been destroyed,

263
00:12:28,550 --> 00:12:31,660
I just don't care what happens anymore.

264
00:12:32,470 --> 00:12:34,390
Isn't there anything we can do?

265
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:37,130
For starters, stop spitting on me.

266
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:39,460
After that, a strong rope.

267
00:12:39,980 --> 00:12:41,020
Hasegawa-san!

268
00:12:42,520 --> 00:12:43,430
I'm kidding.

269
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:48,400
I'm tired... Sorry, but can you all leave now?

270
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:09,440
You're Hasegawa-san, right?

271
00:13:12,680 --> 00:13:14,480
There's something I'd like to talk to you about.

272
00:13:15,250 --> 00:13:16,810
Who are you?

273
00:13:19,140 --> 00:13:25,680
I'm Haga, the prosecutor in the court of law where you will be tried in two days.

274
00:13:26,660 --> 00:13:30,820
In other words Hasegawa-san, I am your enemy.

275
00:13:32,320 --> 00:13:33,130
Prosecutor Haga.

276
00:13:33,560 --> 00:13:38,420
The remarkable prosecutor who has convicted many criminals in examinations.

277
00:13:39,220 --> 00:13:41,420
An elite in the magistrate's office.

278
00:13:41,420 --> 00:13:43,790
The Madao of the past may have been able to deal with him, but now that he's...

279
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:48,240
degraded himself into a sex offender he won't be able to compete with him at all.

280
00:13:48,560 --> 00:13:50,270
That's not true, Kagura.

281
00:13:50,760 --> 00:13:52,660
Hasegawa-san may not have money or luck,

282
00:13:53,090 --> 00:13:54,680
but he's got more guts than anyone I know.

283
00:13:55,220 --> 00:13:56,500
For a man, it's all about heart.

284
00:13:57,050 --> 00:13:58,550
Besides, he didn't commit any lewd acts.

285
00:13:58,880 --> 00:14:00,500
Face reality, Shinpachi.

286
00:14:00,910 --> 00:14:04,700
If you don't have money, you're going to end up unpopular like Gin-chan.

287
00:14:05,360 --> 00:14:06,740
Besides right now, that Madao...

288
00:14:06,970 --> 00:14:09,680
...doesn't even seem to have any guts.

289
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:13,310
He's become a real Madao now.

290
00:14:14,530 --> 00:14:15,830
What is this?

291
00:14:16,160 --> 00:14:19,820
It's exactly what you see...divorce papers for you and Hatsu-san.

292
00:14:20,180 --> 00:14:24,130
I have been going out with Hatsu-san with the intention of marrying her.

293
00:14:24,470 --> 00:14:25,370
What?

294
00:14:25,370 --> 00:14:27,440
You have no right to complain.

295
00:14:28,230 --> 00:14:32,900
I hear you've been separated and practically divorced.

296
00:14:33,880 --> 00:14:36,160
I'd like you to officially put an end to it right here.

297
00:14:36,730 --> 00:14:38,420
Please put your seal on this?

298
00:14:38,420 --> 00:14:39,320
You gotta be kidding me.

299
00:14:39,630 --> 00:14:43,020
Why should I take orders from an outsider like you?

300
00:14:43,150 --> 00:14:46,140
You're no longer related to Hatsu-san either.

301
00:14:46,660 --> 00:14:48,790
Or were you planning on reconciling with her?

302
00:14:49,470 --> 00:14:52,980
Can you, being in a place like this, really make her happy?

303
00:14:54,110 --> 00:14:57,730
Besides, I already told you. I am your enemy.

304
00:14:58,390 --> 00:15:04,220
In two days, I can help decide if you are guilty or not.

305
00:15:04,910 --> 00:15:06,550
I'm sure you understand what I mean.

306
00:15:07,300 --> 00:15:10,230
If you put your seal on this, I promise that you will be proven innocent.

307
00:15:11,150 --> 00:15:12,440
And if you don't...

308
00:15:13,030 --> 00:15:14,260
Well, let's see...

309
00:15:17,170 --> 00:15:21,070
Hasegawa-san, when you left the Department of Immigration Control,

310
00:15:21,070 --> 00:15:25,360
[Note: Seppuku is a form of Japanese ritual suicide by disembowelment.]

311
00:15:21,070 --> 00:15:23,310
I understand the Bakufu ordered you to commit seppuku,

312
00:15:23,310 --> 00:15:25,360
but instead you chose to run away.

313
00:15:26,030 --> 00:15:28,640
I said shut up, you freakin' space flounder!

314
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:30,750
Commit seppuku.

315
00:15:30,750 --> 00:15:32,270
Are you serious?

316
00:15:33,830 --> 00:15:36,660
What will happen if I mention this during the questioning?

317
00:15:37,610 --> 00:15:40,000
Well, most likely your head will roll.

318
00:15:41,450 --> 00:15:44,290
Please give it some serious thought, Hasegawa-san.

319
00:15:44,880 --> 00:15:48,470
Well, in either case, Hatsu-san is mine.

320
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:54,030
And, what awaits you is the life of a loser.

321
00:16:00,230 --> 00:16:01,380
Um, excuse me.

322
00:16:02,940 --> 00:16:05,030
Is this the Odd Jobs?

323
00:16:05,450 --> 00:16:06,450
Yes, it is...

324
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:09,560
Oh, then you must be Gin-san.

325
00:16:11,280 --> 00:16:12,600
My, your hair really is silver.

326
00:16:13,710 --> 00:16:16,670
Thank you for always taking care of Taizo Hasegawa.

327
00:16:17,500 --> 00:16:20,820
I'm Taizo's wife...Hatsu...

328
00:16:33,180 --> 00:16:34,030
Why...

329
00:16:34,790 --> 00:16:36,850
Why am I always like this?

330
00:16:37,690 --> 00:16:40,310
Whenever I try to grab happiness, it runs away...

331
00:16:40,310 --> 00:16:42,850
...at full speed.

332
00:16:46,280 --> 00:16:47,570
That's right...

333
00:16:47,570 --> 00:16:51,130
[Note: Refers to the TV animation version of Heidi.]

334
00:16:47,570 --> 00:16:51,130
It's Heidi. Heidi lives inside of me.

335
00:16:52,920 --> 00:16:55,340
The flowers of happiness are about to bloom,

336
00:16:55,340 --> 00:16:57,390
but an impatient Heidi picks them,

337
00:16:57,390 --> 00:16:59,600
even though they're only buds.

338
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:02,960
[Note: He looks like Peter from the TV animation version of Heidi.]

339
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:02,960
Heidi! It's too early. They haven't blossomed yet.

340
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:07,570
I tried to stop Heidi many times. But she would never listen to

341
00:17:07,570 --> 00:17:09,380
what Peter says.

342
00:17:10,340 --> 00:17:12,470
The only way to put an end to her acts of violence

343
00:17:12,470 --> 00:17:16,900
was to throw myself and her into the ravine of the Alps.

344
00:17:16,930 --> 00:17:20,800
Peter! No! I don't want to leave the mountains!

345
00:17:19,120 --> 00:17:22,240
You must die!

346
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:26,690
That's all I've been thinking about the last few days.

347
00:17:27,730 --> 00:17:29,020
You've got a visitor.

348
00:17:36,360 --> 00:17:39,110
So, did you bring me a rope?

349
00:17:44,120 --> 00:17:48,970
He offered me a deal. That bastard prosecutor who's going out with Hatsu.

350
00:17:51,730 --> 00:17:56,580
[Note: In Japan, an official seal, used like a signature, is stamped on divorce papers.]

351
00:17:51,730 --> 00:17:53,630
He told me to put my seal on the divorce papers.

352
00:17:54,010 --> 00:17:56,580
If I don't, he will make sure my head gets cut off at the trial.

353
00:17:58,500 --> 00:17:59,710
I'm planning on putting my seal on it.

354
00:18:00,500 --> 00:18:04,130
All I'm doing is dragging Hatsu down by not being able to let go

355
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:06,640
and hanging on to this one piece of paper.

356
00:18:07,490 --> 00:18:09,250
I don't want to stand in Hatsu's way

357
00:18:09,250 --> 00:18:12,770
if she's trying to leave her hopeless husband and start a new life.

358
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:15,980
Besides, I don't wanna die.

359
00:18:17,890 --> 00:18:18,990
Go ahead and laugh.

360
00:18:18,990 --> 00:18:22,540
I'm gonna sell off my wife so I can save my precious life.

361
00:18:24,170 --> 00:18:25,030
I...

362
00:18:25,030 --> 00:18:26,090
Your wife came to see me.

363
00:18:27,300 --> 00:18:29,880
She couldn't get in touch with you so she came to see me.

364
00:18:31,780 --> 00:18:34,010
She wanted to wish you good luck on your new job.

365
00:18:34,010 --> 00:18:36,010
And she asked me to give you this.

366
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:38,050
Th-This is...

367
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:42,520
She doesn't know...that I've been arrested?

368
00:18:43,070 --> 00:18:46,630
I don't know. But I haven't told her anything.

369
00:18:47,280 --> 00:18:48,940
Well, that's all I wanted to say. See ya.

370
00:18:51,790 --> 00:18:53,150
Oh yeah, and about that rope.

371
00:18:53,660 --> 00:18:55,480
I'll bring it next time I come.

372
00:18:55,930 --> 00:18:58,970
I have no intention of getting you a rope so you can hang yourself.

373
00:18:59,860 --> 00:19:00,660
But...

374
00:19:01,420 --> 00:19:06,250
If it's a rope to pull you out of hell, then I'll bring you as many as you want.

375
00:19:07,080 --> 00:19:08,190
Just remember that.

376
00:19:21,890 --> 00:19:23,210
Peter!

377
00:19:23,210 --> 00:19:25,240
Peter, you want me to stamp it?

378
00:19:25,450 --> 00:19:28,250
I know you can't do it. I'll do it for you.

379
00:19:28,380 --> 00:19:29,750
You don't wanna die, right?

380
00:19:30,080 --> 00:19:32,420
Heidi!

381
00:19:34,560 --> 00:19:37,880
Yeah, just like that, you keep living your life as a doggone loser.

382
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:39,350
Stop, Heidi!

383
00:19:40,360 --> 00:19:42,220
That's perfect for you.

384
00:19:42,370 --> 00:19:43,340
Joseph!!

385
00:19:42,370 --> 00:19:48,500
[Note: Hasegawa is dressed up as Joseph from the TV animation version of Heidi.]

386
00:19:45,460 --> 00:19:48,500
You're right. I may be a doggone loser...

387
00:19:50,980 --> 00:19:51,790
But!

388
00:19:51,790 --> 00:19:53,570
Even if I'm a worthless mutt...

389
00:19:56,330 --> 00:20:05,050
[From the story "A Dog of Flanders"; a novel and anime about the boy Nello and his dog Patrasche. Nello and Patrasche freeze to death as they go to see Rubens' painting.]

390
00:19:56,330 --> 00:20:00,170
I'm the mutt who goes to see Rubens' painting before I die!!

391
00:20:00,660 --> 00:20:05,050
Just remember, I'll keep coming back!

392
00:20:10,910 --> 00:20:12,460
I gotta fight.

393
00:20:12,820 --> 00:20:14,910
It's all over if a man loses his fangs.

394
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:17,350
Even if I'm just a good-for-nothing mutt,

395
00:20:17,350 --> 00:20:20,620
as long as I've got fangs, I'll keep fighting till the end.

396
00:20:20,820 --> 00:20:23,300
I'll be a dandy man who won't be defeated...

397
00:20:20,820 --> 00:20:23,300
[Note: A MAkenai DAndy na Otoko or a Madao.]

398
00:20:24,700 --> 00:20:25,430
a Madao!

399
00:20:28,460 --> 00:20:34,850
We will now start the trial for the Oedo Line Kinniku Buster molestation case.

400
00:20:35,630 --> 00:20:39,570
The defendant, Taizo Hasegawa, please raise your head.

401
00:20:41,630 --> 00:20:44,470
You must swear on this document

402
00:20:44,900 --> 00:20:49,470
that any testimony you give here is true.

403
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:52,210
If you break this promise,

404
00:20:52,210 --> 00:20:55,520
you will be subject to punishment regardless of the outcome of this trial.

405
00:20:57,130 --> 00:21:00,800
Haga, if you want to cut my head off, then go right ahead.

406
00:21:01,510 --> 00:21:05,880
But, I refuse to hand over Hatsu to a man who uses dirty tricks like you.

407
00:21:06,740 --> 00:21:11,850
Even if my head gets chopped off, I'll bite your throat with just my head.

408
00:21:12,620 --> 00:21:15,420
Hatsu...I will protect Hatsu!

409
00:21:16,740 --> 00:21:17,800
Hang on a second.

410
00:21:18,390 --> 00:21:21,350
Who is representing the defendant? Where is he?

411
00:21:21,750 --> 00:21:24,320
Well...he's not here yet.

412
00:21:24,730 --> 00:21:26,920
Perhaps something happened on his way here.

413
00:21:27,230 --> 00:21:30,070
Oh, sorry. I'm late.

414
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:34,320
Attorney Shimoyama, who was supposed to be here, was arrested on molestation charges,

415
00:21:34,870 --> 00:21:36,170
so I'm his replacement.

416
00:21:42,170 --> 00:21:44,260
I'm the attorney, Sakata.

417
00:21:45,130 --> 00:21:46,990
Nice to meet you.

418
00:21:47,580 --> 00:21:48,790
Gin-san?!

419
00:21:51,420 --> 00:21:53,500
Here? Do I sit here?

420
00:21:53,740 --> 00:21:54,980
Take your shoes off. Your shoes.

421
00:21:56,010 --> 00:21:56,920
Why...?

422
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:00,760
So you're gonna help me fight?

423
00:22:01,850 --> 00:22:03,010
You and me together?

424
00:22:04,220 --> 00:22:06,300
But can an amateur defend me?

425
00:22:06,650 --> 00:22:09,320
So shall we start, Mr. Prosecutor?

426
00:22:10,070 --> 00:22:11,760
We're up against that Prosecutor Haga, you know.

427
00:22:13,660 --> 00:22:16,870
We will now start the trial.

